# Diagramming — {{companyName}}

## When to Use
- Creating architecture diagrams or system design visualizations
- Generating flowcharts, sequence diagrams, or entity-relationship diagrams
- Illustrating deployment topologies or data flows

## Supported Formats
- **Mermaid** — Inline code block diagrams (flowcharts, sequence, class, state, ER, Gantt)
- **Draw.io / diagrams.net** — XML-based diagrams for complex architectures
- **Excalidraw** — Hand-drawn style diagrams for brainstorming and whiteboarding
- **PlantUML** — Text-based UML diagrams

## Best Practices
- Use Mermaid for simple diagrams that embed in markdown
- Use Excalidraw for collaborative whiteboarding and brainstorming
- Use Draw.io for detailed, production-quality architecture diagrams
- Include diagram source files alongside rendered images for version control
- Follow {{companyName}} color palette when generating branded diagrams
